Nairobi, Kenya: Amani&rsquo;s Musalia Mudavadi and KANU Secretary General Nick Salat join CORD leaders at Bomas of Kenya to unveil a united Opposition front.Opposition leaders are expected to announce the structure of the much-touted National Super Alliance (Nasa). CORD principals Raila Odinga, Kalonzo Musyoka and Moses Wetang&rsquo;ula and Amani National Congress (ANC) leader Musalia Mudavadi as well as leaders of Kanu are meeting at the Bomas of Kenya to discuss Nasa&rsquo;s leadership and organisation. Later on, they will meet over 3,000 delegates to brief them on progress they will have made in their spirited efforts to send President Uhuru Kenyatta home in August 8. The Opposition parties have summoned their governors, senators, MPs, MCAs and aspirants to Bomas of Kenya, where they said they will make a major pronouncement.Proposals that the leaders are set to float include what the Nasa slogan will be, its structure and leadership, among others. ALSO READ: Cleric criticises Sossion, Raila for KCSE audit call